<font color="#FF0000">RESTORATION IS NECESSARY</font><br>
<tt>Tue Dec  2 13:25:13 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
We as adults have a responsibility to conduct ourselves as such.  The problem arises about the different versions of what is expected of adults.  The real reason we have used this site and need it now is to define what we are and why we, as adults, suffer from experiences that the many Americans want to put behind them.  We struggle against the unreasonable idea that we should sit down and shut-up.  We were an aberration, an unwanted blip in history that no one wants to deal with.<br><br>
We owe it to ourselves to exhibit this slice of Americana exactly the way it is.  During the war the protesters were at the front of the ranks and the soldier was the dutiful silent minority.  The positive press was normally for the protester or the anti-war enthusiast.  This created a derision between the soldier and the American public because he was held as something distasteful.  Tainted from his wrongful behavior. <br>
A “Baby Killer”, a murderer.  That statement is one that cuts to the soul of every soldier.<br><br>
To not plainly exhibit the threads that are a mirror of where this all started would be a mistake.  This type of character had to be brought to the surface.  To take it away now sets back the entire healing process.  It is time that men and women from all positions deserve to be judged openly on their convictions exhibited here only by their words.  To look at the world through “Rose colored glasses” is clearly wrong.<br><br>
There has been an incredible amount of growth on this site.  We have agreed to disagree and many of us have found positions of acceptance based on individual respect.  We have arrived at a point in time where we have seen a glimpse of the real attitude that creates desperation in the Vet.  The public needs to see the types of behavior that should be avoided and the reality that there are those who just hate the soldier and are still seeking his demise at any cost.<br><br>
I propose that the lost threads be restored and we deal with the problem.  Let the public see why this site was shut down for a period of time.  A time to reflect on the idea of, are during more harm than good.  The strength of the metal is a product of the heat of the fire.<br><br>
Reality can be a cruel mistress, but one we are married to “till death do us part.”<br>

